|alAt a workbench, select the type of item you wish to craft. You must have the appropriate ingredients to select an item.nnWeapons and armor require you to choose a racial style and racial ingredient (available at nearby merchants). nnAt the start you only know the style of your race. You can learn the styles of other races through books discovered in the world.

|alAdvancing a tradeskill is done by deconstructing items and gaining inspiration points in that tradeskill. nnDeconstructing your own crafted items gives few if any inspiration points. Deconstructing another player's crafted items or items found via adventuring give you the most inspiration.nnWhen you accumulate enough inspiration in a given tradeskill, you automatically advance to the next rank and can craft using more advanced materials.

Resources that you gather are typically in their raw form. Most of the time it requires 3 raw materials to make 1 ingredient.nnRaw materials must be taken to a specific crafting table to be worked into their refined form. nn-	Metal  - Anvil, Armorsmith tablen-	Wood - Anviln-	Leather - Armorsmith tablen-	Cloth - Armorsmith tablen-	Gems - Enchanter tablen-	Flowers - Alchemy tablen-	Mushrooms - Alchemy tablen-	Water - Alchemy table, Cooking firen-	Cooking material - Cooking fire

|alOnce you have selected the type of item you want to make, you next must add in ingredients.nnEach item type uses different ingredients. For example swords use Metals and Leathers, while Light robes use Cloth and Leathers.nnThe more ingrediants you use the better the item becomes.nnRemember: Crafting Stations can pull ingredients and additives directly from your account bank.  Store materials in your bank to free up inventory slots.

|alAdditive materials, when used in crafted items, will often improve the quality of the item. The more additives you use the better the quality of the item. nnCombining three different additives together can imbue the crafted item with additional special properties.nnWhen you first find an additive, you will not know what special properties it has.  Use three different additives in different items and combinations to discover its special properties.nnRemember: Crafting Stations can pull ingredients and additives directly from your account bank.  Store materials in your bank to free up inventory slots.

Additive materials, when used in crafted items, will always improve the quality of the item. The more additives you use the better the quality of the item. nnCombining three different additives together can imbue the crafted item with additional special properties.nnWhen you first find an additive, you will not know what special properties it has.  Use three different additives in different items and combinations to discover its special properties.

Transitus Shrines allow you to fast travel in Cyrodiil. Approach a Transitus Shrine and press <<1>>. Then select a keep, gate, or outpost on your map with an unbroken link between where you are and where you want to fast travel.
Aim siege weapons with your mouse:n• Press <<1>> to Fire.n• Press <<2>> to Stow Siege Weapons for future use.n• Exit a siege weapon by pressing <<3>>.

To repair keep walls, keep doors, or siege weapons, you must first place a proper repair kit in a quickslot:n• Hold <<1>> to choose the proper repair kit.n• Press <<1>> to begin repairs.n• You can't repair anything that was recently damaged.
When killed by another player in Cyrodiil, you may revive at any of your alliance's keeps or Forward Camps that aren't under attack. An allied Player may also revive you with a filled Soul Gem.

Before you can deploy your ballista, you must place it in a quickslot:n• Hold <<1>> to choose the ballista.n• Press <<1>> to begin deployment.n• Move the target over flat terrain.n• Press <<2>> to deploy.

Forward Camps allow you to revive outside of the Transitus Shrine network, including within enemy territory. When placed, only your alliance can see the location of a Forward Camp on the map. Forward Camps have a limited number of revivals, so choose carefully.
Elder Scrolls are of prime importance to every alliance. Holding Elder Scrolls at the scroll temples or on a keep's scroll pedestal confers bonuses to every player of that alliance.
Much activity in Cyrodiil centers around capturing the enemy's keeps and resources. See the Bonuses section of the Alliance War tab for details on how holding keeps benefits your alliance.

Cyrodiil's map shows the major objectives in Cyrodiil, Transitus links between objectives, and any locales you discover.nnMove your cursor over a keep or resource to display detailed information. Keeps or resources under attack are outlined with a starburst.nnIcons for points-of-interest and Forward Camp area pins can be toggled on or off by selecting Filters.
The scoreboard can be accessed by pressing "P." The scoreboard displays the current status of the campaign you're currently in. This includes time remaining, score and objectives held.

To go to Cyrodiil, select a campaign and press |t0:0:EsoUI/Art/Miscellaneous/icon_RMB.dds|t. Then choose "Home" to confirm you Home Campaign.nnOnce you have a Home Campaign, select it and press |t0:0:EsoUI/Art/Miscellaneous/icon_RMB.dds|t. Then choose "Enter Campaign" to travel to Cyrodiil.nnAny benefits from keeps or Elder Scrolls held are linked to your Home Campaign. You are welcome to join another campaign as a Guest.nnPress <<1>> for more information.
Alliance Points (APs) are earned by aiding your alliance in Cyrodiil. Killing enemy players, capturing or defending keeps, and capturing Elder Scrolls are some ways to earn APs.
To fish press and hold <<1>> and select the bait you wish to use. nnOnce you have selected the bait, target the fishing hole and press <<1>>.

To gain an advantage in battle, players can hire mercenaries. Their contracts can be purchased from mercenary merchants at the alliance entry gates.nnThe contract can be used from a quickslot. A reticle shows where they can be placed.
Press <<1>> when standing near doors, objects, and people to interact with them.
Press <<1>> to Attack.nHold <<1>> to Charge a Heavy Attack.
Approach and Press <<1>> to Interrupt Special Attacks.

Move the lockpick over a pin and hold |t0:0:EsoUI/Art/Miscellaneous/icon_LMB.dds|t. Release |t0:0:EsoUI/Art/Miscellaneous/icon_LMB.dds|t when the pin wiggles to set it in place. Set all pins before the timer runs out.nnYou can attempt to force the lock by pressing <<1>>.

• Dying damages your armor. Repair it at any store, or purchase a Repair Kit from Merchants.n• Press <<1>> to revive here. Level 6+ characters require a filled Soul Gem.n• Press <<2>> to revive at a Wayshrine.

Deploy your ram to smash a keep's main doors. First, place it in a quickslot:n• Hold <<1>> to choose the ram.n• Press <<1>> to begin deployment.n• Press <<2>> to deploy on flat terrain.n• Rams require three players to move.
Bounty missions send you on quests to kill players of other alliances. Only enemy players count toward these quests.
There are pockets of natural resources, scattered throughout the world, that can be harvested and refined into ingredients and additives for crafting.

Items can be bought and sold through stores.nnIn the Buy menu, items available to purchase from the store are displayed.n - Mouse over items to see their properties.n - Press <<1>> to buy the item.n - Right click the item to bring up a list of actions for that item.nnIn the Sell menu, items available to sell from your inventory are displayed..n- Mouse over items to see their properties.n - Press <<1>> to sell the item.n - Right click the item to bring up a list of actions for that item.nnRemember:n - You can buy back items recently sold.n - Consider deconstructing items you cannot use at a crafting station for crafting inspiration.

Your bank stores items for all of your characters to share:n• Press <<1>> to purchase more bank space.n• Press <<2>> to deposit or withdraw gold.nnCrafting materials stored in your bank are pulled directly to you when crafting. You do not need to carry them to a crafting station.

Achievements track the long term goals important to your account and your characters.  Completing achievements can unlock special rewards.nnRemember:n - The Skyshard section provides hints to Skyshard locations.

Participants in the Alliance War are tracked and ranked based on participation and conquests.nnKilling enemies, taking or defending keeps, and capturing Elder Scrolls are some of the ways to improve your standing.

Select an item to view its properties:n• Press <<1>> to equip or use an item.n• Press |t0:0:EsoUI/Art/Miscellaneous/icon_RMB.dds|t when selecting an item to view other actions.n• Mark unwanted items as junk. You can quickly sell all junk items at any store.

In Town:n• Sell your items at any store.n• Store items in your account bank.n• Purchase backpack space from a Pack Merchant.nnWhile Adventuring:n• Sell your items to a Traveling Merchant.n• Get rid of items you don't need! Press |t0:0:EsoUI/Art/Miscellaneous/icon_RMB.dds|t when selecting an item, then choose Destroy to remove it permanently.
You have acquired a weapon swap.  You can equip an alternate set of weapons with accompanying abilities in this weapon swap.

Use quickslots to easily access potions and other items:n• Press <<1>>, then select Quickslots in the upper right corner. Drag items to the desired slot.nnSelecting an Active Quickslot:n• Hold <<2>> to bring up your Quickslots.n• Select the desired item and release <<2>>nnUsing Quickslot Items:n•  Press <<2>> to use the item in your quickslot.

• Press <<1>> to change your focused quest.n• Press <<2>> to see where to perform the next task.n• Press <<3>> to abandon the focused quest.nnRemember:n• People with the |t32:32:EsoUI/Art/Compass/quest_available_icon.dds|t above them can provide new quests. n• If you're stuck on a quest, check the Quest Journal for hints.nnThe Lore Library contains special books you collect on your journeys throughout Tamriel. Achievements displays hints (such as Skyshard locations) and long term goals that can unlock special rewards for your account and characters (such as dyes). Leaderboards track top players in the Alliance War and Trials.
Your Lore Library is the collection of books that you find throughout Tamriel.

When your characters have a mount set as Active, each character can take riding lessons provided by the local Stablemaster for a small amount of gold. nnSpeak to the Stablemaster to bring up the interface for riding lessons, then press the "+" symbol located next to the desired skill to increase it.nnOne riding lesson will be offered by the Stablemaster every 24 hours, so don't forget to visit the stables daily.

|t0:0:EsoUI/Art/Buttons/pointsPlus_up.dds|t Spend available attribute points to increase your effectiveness in combat.nn• Health increases your survivabilityn• Magicka increases your effectiveness with spellsn• Stamina increases your effectiveness with featsnnPress <<1>> to commit points.

You have Attribute Points available to spend. Press |t0:0:EsoUI/Art/Buttons/pointsPlus_up.dds|t to spend them:n• Magicka increases your effectiveness with class abilities.n• Health increases your survivability in combat.n• Stamina improves most weapon abilities.nnOnce spent, press <<1>> to permanently commit the Attribute Points.

Browse different skill lines to customize your combat style:n• Select abilities to learn what they do.n• Press |t32:32:EsoUI/Art/Progression/addPoints_up.dds|t to purchase an ability.n• To use an Active Ability you purchased, drag it onto your ability tray.

Track the progress of your character's  trade skills.nnEventually you will not be able to gain inspiration in a trade skill without losing it in another.  Manage the potential gains and losses of inspiration in this interface.

The compass shows your current quest objectives with|t32:32:EsoUI/Art/Compass/quest_icon_assisted.dds|t or |t32:32:EsoUI/Art/Compass/quest_icon_door_assisted.dds|t If you get lost, press <<1>> to open your Map.

Each of your characters and any guilds you may be in are committed to a campaign. Characters can be moved to another campaign or a character can fight in another campaign as a guest.nnGuild leaders can manage the campaign assignment of the guild they lead. Members can join this campaign and take keeps and resources in the name of their guild.
Press <<1>> to open your Character Menu and increase your effectiveness in combat.

You have found a second Wayshrine.  You can use the fast travel network to travel instantly between wayshrines.nnRemember:n - You can always travel to a Wayshrine you have found for a small price from anywhere.  If ever you feel lost, open the map and travel to a friendly destination.

Add friends to your contact list so you can stay in touch:n• Press <<1>> to Add Friend. Type the character name or @UserID of the person you want to add.n• Select a contact and press <<2>> to whisper. Press <<3>> to Invite to Group. (Characters must share the same alliance.)n• Select a contact and press |t0:0:EsoUI/Art/Miscellaneous/icon_RMB.dds|t for additional options.nnRemember:n• If another player bothers you, press |t0:0:EsoUI/Art/Miscellaneous/icon_RMB.dds|t on their name and choose "Ignore" to block all future interactions.n• Press |t32:32:EsoUI/Art/Tutorial/tutorial_illo_status_online.dds|t to change your status to "Offline" when you wish to take a break from your contacts.

• Press <<1>> to Invite Player to a group. Type the character name or @UserID of the person you want to add.n• Select the Grouping Tool to find other players who want to adventure in groups. Group leaders can use Looking for Members to fill out your group.n• Change your Preferred Role to designate what group role you plan to fulfill.nnRemember:n• Grouping allows you to team up against harder enemiesn• All group members gain a 10% bonus to experience gained

While solo, you can use the Join a Group tool to find a group engaged in content you wish to explore.nnAs a group leader, you can use the Looking for Members tool to fill out your group with other adventurers.
Press <<1>> to open your Mail menu.
Someone is trying to speak privately with you. Type "/whisper" followed by their @UserID (or select their name in the chat window) to respond.
Your equipment loses durability each time you die. You can pay to repair it at any store, or purchase a Repair Kit from Merchants to keep your equipment at its best performance.
One of your magical items is out of charges. You can replenish its magical properties with a filled Soul Gem.

To repair a keep wall, place a <<1>> in a quickslot:n• Hold <<2>> to choose the repair kit.n• Target the damaged keep wall.n• Press <<2>> to repair the keep wall.n• You can't repair recently damaged walls.

Before you can deploy your catapult, you must place it in a quickslot:n• Hold <<1>> to choose the catapult.n• Press <<1>> to begin catapult deployment.n• Move the target over flat terrain.n• Press <<2>> to deploy.

Before you can deploy your trebuchet, you must place it in a quickslot:n• Hold <<1>> to choose the trebuchet.n• Press <<1>> to begin trebuchet deployment.n• Move the target over flat terrain.n• Press <<2>> to deploy.

You discovered a group dungeon. It is best to adventure in these areas with a group. Group dungeons are private so only other group members can enter with you.nnRemember:n• Press <<1>> to open the Group window, then press <<2>> to invite other players.
You discovered a public dungeon. These areas of increased difficulty are best explored with others. You do not need to be in a group to enter a public dungeon with other players.

You have equipped armor.nnWhile all armor adds protection, different armor types have special benefits.nnAdventuring in armor of a specific type will increase skill in that armor. This unlocks abilities that improve the armor's benefits.

You have equipped a weapon.nnBasic Moves:n• Press <<1>> to execute a light attack.n• Hold <<1>> to execute a heavy attack.n• Hold <<2>> to take a defensive posture and block incoming attacks.nnAdvanced Technique:n• Approach and press <<3>> to interrupt enemies who are attempting a special attack.
You have collected a material usefull in crafting goods.

• Press <<1>>, then select the disguise.n• Press <<2>> to equip your disguise.nnRemember:n• Some enemies can see through disguises.n• You cannot sneak while disguised.n• Engaging in combat removes disguises.
The Mail window allows you to send and receive in-game mail.nnRemember:n• Delete messages you no longer need. You only have a set number of Mail slots.
Delete messages to free up some space so that you can begin receiving mail again.
Invitations to guilds and contacts are moved to the notifications window if you cannot answer them right away. This allows you to receive invitations while offline, in combat, or otherwise busy.
You can safely trade items and gold with other players. Make sure you are happy with the trade before you accept it.

The guild bank is a shared storage area where you and your guild members can place items.nnRemember:n• Don't share precious goods that you don't want to be taken and used by others. The guild bank is a communal resource and items placed here can and will be taken.n• Use the guild history to view a log of items and those who have deposited and withdrawn them.n• If the guild bank is not accessible, make sure you have the appropriate permissions and the guild is large enough to unlock it.

• Press <<1>> to add members to the Roster tab.n• Press <<2>> to add ranks on the Ranks tab.nnRemember:n• Type "/guild1" or "/g1" in the chat window to speak in guild chat. If you are a member of more than one guild, type "/g2", "/g3", "/g4", or "/g5" to switch guild chat channels.n• You can join up to five guilds, but you can only lead one.n• All of your characters have access to your guilds, but only those matching a guild's alliance can capture keeps and resources for them in Cyrodiil
The Guild Roster window allows you to view and manage the guild's membership.
The ability you purchased has been added to your ability tray.nn• Press <<1>> to use the ability.n• Some abilities require a valid target, such as an ally or an enemy.

You purchased an Ultimate Ability. Drag it to the Ultimate Ability slot in the ability tray to use it during combat.nnUltimate Abilities require a special resource called Ultimate before they can be used. Gain Ultimate by engaging in combat. Once you have enough Ultimate, you can use the Ultimate Ability in combat by pressing <<1>>.

Wayshrines are a fast and inexpensive way to travel.nn•  Approach any Wayshrine and press <<1>> to bring up your map. Select any Wayshrine you have previously discovered to fast travel to that location. There is no cost to fast travel directly from Wayshrine to Wayshrine.n•  Press <<2>> and select any previously discovered Wayshrine to fast travel there from anywhere in the world. There is a nominal cost to fast travel directly to a Wayshrine.nnRemember: if you ever feel lost, open your map and select a Wayshrine to fast travel to a friendly destination.
You can now equip an additional set of weapons and ability tray. Press <<1>> to peform the Weapon Swap.

•  Press <<1>> to ride your mount.n•  Hold <<2>> while mounted to gallop.n•  Press <<3>> while mounted to jump.n•  Press <<1>> while mounted to dismount.nnTalk to any Stablemaster to manage and improve your mounts.

You discovered a skyshard. Skyshards are scattered across the lands of Tamriel. For every three Skyshards you collect, your character gains an extra Skill Point.nnPress <<1>> to find hints to Skyshard locations in your Achievements Journal.
Refined ingredients can be used to craft items. Use the Create screen to start crafting a new item.

Perform a sneak attack to destroy the Sentinel.nPress <<1>> to Sneak
You have 1 minute before the hoard arrives.
Bring Glowing Shards to the THREE Shrines.
Enter the Portal at the Temple.

Campaigns scores are evaluated regularly. Your alliance gains Campaign Points based on the keeps, outposts, resources, and Elder Scrolls it possesses when the campaign is scored. If one alliance outpaces the others by a large margin, the lower-scoring alliances will receive scoring bonuses against the lead alliance.nnWhen your campaign ends, you are rewarded based on the number of Alliance Points you earned in your Home Campaign, your Leaderboard status, and how well your alliance did in the campaign.
|t32:32:EsoUI/Art/ChatWindow/chat_notification_echo.dds|t You have received a Notification.n[N] to manage Notifications
|t32:32:EsoUI/Art/Quest/questJournal_trackedQuest_icon.dds|t  Completing quest objectives will advance your character's story.  Active quests are tracked at the top right of the screen.
Cadwell's Almanac allows players to keep track of their progress during their Veteran Alliance playthroughs.
You gained a Bind on Equip item. Once equipped to any of your characters, it is bound to characters on your account. You cannot trade or sell it to other players.
You purchased a Passive Ability. They are always active, granting you their benefits at all times. Passive Abilities cannot be placed in the ability tray.

You have entered a scaled area which is scaled to the level or Veteran Rank of you, or your party leader if you are in a group. Monster levels/ranks and difficulty are adjusted to reflect this.nnItems rewarded from monsters, chests and other sources will be scaled as well. Items will scale to your level or the monster's level, whichever is lower.
You received a Soul Gem. Recharge magical weapons, revive allies, or revive yourself with Soul Gems.

• Select Weapons or Apparel, then choose the type of item you wish to craft.n• Select a Material and a Style. (Traits are not required, but you can select any you have researched.)n• Press <<1>> to Craft.nnRemember:n• Add more raw materials to increase item level and effectiveness.n• You can only craft styles you know, and style materials are required to craft. Purchase them from any blacksmith.

• Select Weapons or Apparel, then choose the item you wish to improve.n• Press <<1>> to Add the item.n• Press <<2>> to Improve, or press <<3>> to Clear Selection.nnRemember:n• Tempers are required for improvement.n• If you don't use enough tempers, the item may be destroyed in the process!n• Unequip items you wish to improve. Equipped items can't be improved.

• Select Weapons or Apparel, then choose the item you wish to deconstruct.n• Press <<1>> to Add the item.n• Press <<2>> to Deconstruct, or press <<3>> to Clear Selection.nnRemember:n• Deconstruction destroys the item! Only deconstruct unwanted items.n• Deconstructing returns some of an item's components.n• Unequip items you wish to deconstruct. Equipped items can't be deconstructed.

• Select Weapons or Apparel, then choose the item you wish to research.n• Press <<1>> to Research.nnRemember:n• Research destroys the item! Only research unwanted items.n• When crafting, adding Traits requires an associated gemstone. These can be found from adventuring, mining, or deconstructing weapons with identical Traits.n• Unequip items you wish to research. Equipped items can't be researched.

Purchase them from any clothier.

Equipped items can't be improved.

These can be found from adventuring, mining, or deconstructing weapons with identical Traits.n• Unequip items you wish to research. Equipped items can't be researched.

• Select Weapons or Apparel, then choose the item you wish to improve.n• Press <<1>> to Add the item.n• Press <<2>> to Improve, or press <<3>> to Clear Selection.nnRemember:n• Resins are required for improvement.n• If you don't use enough resins, the item may be destroyed in the process!n• Unequip items you wish to improve. Equipped items can't be improved.

• Select a rune and press <<1>> to Add the item.n• Add one of each rune: Potency (blue square), Essence (green triangle), and Aspect (orange circle).n• Press <<2>> to Craft, or press <<3>> to Clear Selections.nnRemember:n• Glyphs formed by runes can be applied to weapons, apparel, or jewelry.n• Crafting unknown runes allows you to learn their effects.

• Select the glyph you wish to extract.n• Press <<1>> to Add the glyph.n• Press <<2>> to Extract, or press <<3>> to Clear Selection.nnRemember:n• Extraction destroys the glyph! Only extract unwanted glyphs.n• Extracting returns some of a glyph's runes.

• Select Cook or Brew, then choose the item you want to make.nn• Press <<1>> to Craft.nnRemember:n• You can only craft food and drink if you learn the associated recipe. Recipes can be found while adventuring.n• You need all of a recipe's ingredients before you can craft it.

• Select a Solvent and press <<1>> to Add.n• Select two different Reagents and press <<1>> to Add.n• Press <<2>> to Craft, or press <<3>> to Clear Selections.nnRemember:n• Each Reagent has four Traits. Match Reagents with similar Traits to create potions.n• Select a Reagent in your inventory and press <<1>> to consume it and learn its first Trait.n• If no Reagent Traits match, you lose Reagents and Solvent!

Now that you've reached Level 10, you can enter the PvP battlefields of Cyrodiil. Press <<1>> to open the Alliance War. Select the Campaigns icon on the upper right to see the list of available campaigns.

To begin crafting, blacksmiths must refine raw materials:n• Collect 10 raw materials (such as iron ore)n• Select the raw material and press <<1>>n• Press <<1>> to Refine, or press <<2>> to Clear Selection.nnRemember:n• Once you have refined enough raw materials, select "Creation" in the upper right of the tab to craft an item.

To begin crafting, clothiers must refine raw materials:n• Collect 10 raw materials (such as raw jute or leather scraps)n• Select the raw material and press <<1>>n• Press <<1>> to Refine, or press <<2>> to Clear Selection.nnRemember:n• Once you have refined enough raw materials, select "Creation" in the upper right of the tab to craft an item.

To begin crafting, woodworkers must refine raw materials:n• Collect 10 raw materials (such as rough maple)n• Select the raw material and press <<1>>n• Press <<1>> to Refine, or press <<2>> to Clear Selection.nnRemember:n• Once you have refined enough raw materials, select "Creation" in the upper right of the tab to craft an item.
You have just accepted a daily quest. These quests can be completed only once per day.
Congratulations! You and your group have completed a Trial. Be sure to check out the Trial Leaderboards to see where you rank.
Your group has run out of souls and is unable to continue this Trial. You will respawn at the staging area where you can choose to start the Trial again from the beginning.
Face the fiercest encounters Tamriel has to offer! Complete them as fast as you and your group can to earn a place within the top 100 on the Trial Leaderboards.
Difficult monsters you encounter will have unique Health bars. The more lavish the Health bar, the harder the monster.
You have been targeted by a Status Effect. The appearance of your Health, Stamina, and Magicka bar changes when there is a Status Effect upon you.

You received an empty Soul Gem. To fill it, use the Soul Trap ability on an enemy moments before the enemy's death. Press <<1>> to open your Skills and find the Soul Trap ability in the Soul Magic skill line.
You cannot loot any more items. Clear inventory space to loot more.
Your inventory is full and you cannot accept the quest reward. Clear out some inventory space.

You can now purchase an Ultimate Ability in one of your skill lines. These powerful abilities can often turn the tide of battle. When you have a Skill Point available, you can press <<1>> to open your Skills and purchase the Ultimate Ability.
You have joined a group. To chat to your party members type /g.
You joined a Group. To chat with your Group members, type "/p" in the chat window.
To chat with your Guild members, type "/guild1" or "/g1" in the chat window.nnIf you belong to multiple Guilds, type "/g2", "/g3", "/g4", or "/g5" in the chat window to select the appropriate Guild.
Your character now has Eidetic Memory and will remember all notes, books, or letters your character has read (or will read).nnPress <<1>> and select Lore Library to view your new collection!

•	The Paint Brush and Bucket dye tools will allow you to apply dyes to your armornn•	The Eraser and Eye Dropper dye tools will allow you to erase dyes from specific slots and copy existing colors from other slotsnn•	When you gain access to a specific dye, the lock icon in front of that dye will be removednn•	Right-click on any locked dye to discover how you can unlock it
Veteran Ranks reward you an Attribute Point as well as a
Press <<1>> to loot objects in the world.
Some chests and doors are locked. Press <<1>> to try and lockpick them.
You discovered an entrance to Imperial City. Access to the Imperial City is gated by owning your natively owned six keeps for your alliance.
Approach and Press <<1>> to Interrupt Special Attacks.
Hold <<1>> to Charge a Heavy Attack.
While hidden, press <<1>> to perform a Sneak Attack
Follow the pips on your compass to continue your quest. You can cycle through quests you have by pressing <<1>>.

You have acquired a bounty, which is the gold value you must pay to clear your name. Until then, avoid the Guard.nn• You gain a bounty whenever a witness observes you committing a crime. If you aren't witnessed, you do not gain a bounty.n• You can pay your bounty to a fence in any Outlaws Refuge (|t32:32:EsoUI/Art/Icons/mapKey/mapKey_fence.dds|t). You can also pay your bounty to a Guard, but any stolen goods you possess will be confiscated.n• Your bounty will slowly decrease with the passage of time.

Fences |t32:32:EsoUI/Art/Icons/mapKey/mapKey_fence.dds|t can be found in any outlaws refuge. Fences provide specialized services to the outlaws of Tamriel.nn•	You can only sell stolen items to a fence. You will receive a portion of the item's full value.n•	If you find a stolen item you wish to keep, you can pay the fence to launder it. This will remove all evidence of a crime, allowing you to safely keep and use the item.n•	You can sell or launder a limited number of items per day.

While crouched, you can pick the pockets of some citizens. Patience and quick reflexes are essential.nn• Crouch directly behind your target and wait for the right moment to increase your chance of success.n• When you are ready, press <<1>>n• Picking pockets is a crime. You will gain a bounty if you fail, or if a witness observes your attempt.

Locked doors keep outlaws away from valuables. Successfully picking the lock is a crime known as breaking and entering.nn• You must have at least one lockpick |t32:32:EsoUI/Art/Icons/lockpick.dds|t to pick a lock.n • Press <<1>> to pick a locked door. You will gain a bounty if a witness sees you successfully pick the lock.n• Some citizens reside behind locked doors. If they witness you commit a crime, you will gain a bounty.
Congratulations! You have proven yourself worthy of the title, Champion. Press <<1>> to gaze upon the stars and choose your destiny.
You gained a Champion Point. Go to the Champion System Menu by pressing <<1>> and spend your point within the appropriate Constellation.

The Champion System Menu allows you to assign Champion Points to the various Constellations to attain statistical bonuses. nnPoints are earned in sequential order, starting with the first point being earned in the Warrior Constellation, followed by the Thief Constellation and the Mage Constellation. Once Champion Points are earned, they can be spent at any time in the appropriate Constellation. nnTo spend points, select a Minor Constellation by rotating around the interface with the Mouse, and use the <<1>> key to zoom in.  nnEvery Champion Point spent in a Minor Constellation will increase its rank. When a Minor Constellation reaches an appropriate rank, passive abilities will automatically unlock for your character.

You stole from someone. Law-abiding witnesses will give you a bounty. Guards will confiscate stolen items unless you successfully flee.nn• You can sell stolen items to a fence in any Outlaws Refuge |t32:32:EsoUI/Art/Icons/mapKey/mapKey_fence.dds|tn• Using stolen items (such as food or potions) won't give you a bounty. Crafting with stolen materials produces "clean" crafted items.n• Stolen gold is never confiscated!

You are now disreputable. The Guard is aware of your bounty.nn• Guards who see you will give chase and attempt to arrest you.n• Guards cannot be killed, but you can escape them. Flee the area or hide in an Outlaws Refuge |t32:32:EsoUI/Art/Icons/mapKey/mapKey_fence.dds|tn• You can clear your bounty by paying a Guard who arrests you or a fence in an Outlaws Refuge.

You are now notorious. The Guard is aware of your bounty and will actively seek to arrest you.nn• Some citizens will refuse to speak with you until you clear your bounty. n• Guards cannot be killed, but you can escape them. Flee the area or hide in an Outlaws Refuge |t32:32:EsoUI/Art/Icons/mapKey/mapKey_fence.dds|tn• You can clear your bounty by paying a Guard who arrests you or a fence in an Outlaws Refuge.

You are a wanted fugitive! Guards who spot you will actively seek to kill you.nn• Guards cannot be killed, but you can escape them. Flee the area or hide in an Outlaws Refuge |t32:32:EsoUI/Art/Icons/mapKey/mapKey_fence.dds|tn• Clear your bounty by paying a fence in any Outlaws Refuge.n• Some citizens will refuse to speak with you until you clear your bounty.

You equipped a stolen item. Guards who arrest you will confiscate stolen items unless you successfully flee.nn• Confiscated weapons will leave you empty-handed. Confiscated clothing or armor will leave you undefended.n• You can pay a fence in any Outlaws Refuge |t32:32:EsoUI/Art/Icons/mapKey/mapKey_fence.dds|t to launder items you wish to keep. Doing so removes their stolen status. Laundered items are never confiscated.
You killed someone's livestock. Law-abiding witnesses will give you a bounty.

• Each Outlaws Refuge has multiple exits. One exit always leads to an area where the Guard doesn't patrol.n• Fences buy stolen goods, launder stolen items you wish to keep, and help you pay your bounty.n• Many of the larger cities throughout Tamriel have an Outlaws Refuge. Be sure to find the closest one before you begin a crime spree.

You can only sell stolen items to a fence, found in any Outlaws Refuge |t32:32:EsoUI/Art/Icons/mapKey/mapKey_fence.dds|tn• Using stolen items (such as food or potions) won't give you a bounty. Crafting with stolen materials produces "clean" crafted items.n• You cannot store stolen items in your bank. If you wish to keep a stolen item, you must first launder it at a fence.

The Collections Menu is home to all of your accounts' Collections and DLC packs. Collections include wearable Costumes, non-combat Pets, and Mounts. Whenever you obtain a new collectible it can be found and set as active within this menu. nn	•	To set a Collectible as active, right-click the preferred collectible and select the "Set Active" optionnnCollectibles can also be assigned to a Quickslot via the Quickslot submenu.

The Crown Store allows you to purchase customization and convenience items, as well as DLC for your Elder Scrolls Online: Tamriel Unlimited account. All transactions in the Crown Store are made with the store currency, known as Crowns.n n	•	Crowns can be purchased using the "Buy Crowns" button located in the lower left corner of the Crown Store menunnPurchase of any DLC or Non-Consumable Item in the Crown Store will give you access to that DLC or Item forever. Consumable Items are level agnostic and will operate at the level of the character using them.
